Chapter 1:
- Habits are the compound interest of self-improvement. Getting 1 percent better every day counts for a lot in the long-run.
- Habits are the double-edged swords which can help or against you.
- Small changes only make different when you cross the critical threadhold. The powerful outcome of compond process is always delayed. You must be patient.
- Am atomic habit is a piece of a large system
- If you want a better result, forget the goal, focus on improve and maintain the system process

